The best bet is really a SCSI CD-RW
The CD-RW has a laser with AGC (auto gain control), and my Ricoh seems
to be able to read and copy some disks that my friends Panasonic 4X and
Creative 2X can not.
Parallel port is a VERY poor choice. Go with SCSI and a Docking station
or PCMCIA SCSI.

